        <h1>LeetCode 611: Valid Triangle Number (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                Given an integer array nums, return the number of triplets chosen from the array that can make triangles if we take them as side lengths of a triangle. For three sides to form a valid triangle, they must satisfy the triangle inequality: the sum of any two sides must be greater than the third side.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: nums = [2,2,3,4] → Output: 3. Valid combinations are: (2,3,4) using first 2, (2,3,4) using second 2, and (2,2,3).
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    int triangleNumber(vector&lt;int&gt;&amp; nums) {
        sort(nums.begin(), nums.end());
        int n = nums.size();
        int count = 0;
        
        for (int k = n - 1; k &gt;= 2; k--) {
            int i = 0;
            int j = k - 1;
            
            while (i &lt; j) {
                if (nums[i] + nums[j] &gt; nums[k]) {
                    count += j - i;
                    j--;
                } else {
                    i++;
                }
            }
        }
        
        return count;
    }
};</code></pre>
